1)This command is used to create a docker container if somebdy have already created a yml files
docker compose up --build -d

2)This command is used when we already have used the 1) command and want to rerun it. This command runs all the containers that is specified in the docker-compose.yml file
docker compose up -d

3)This command is used to stop the docker container
docker compose down

4)This commands shows the number of images of docker
docker images

5)This commmad shows the conatiner that is currently running
docker ps

6)This command shows all the container available
docker ps -a

7)This command is used to remove or destroy then docker image
docker rmi Image_Name

8)This command is used to remove or destroy the docker container
docker rm Container_Name

9)This command is used for port binding
docker run -p8080:3306 Image_Name     (Where 8080 is the local machine port and 3306 is container port)




------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

For DockerHub

1)This command is used to pull the image from the dockerHUb
docker pull IMAGE_NAME

2The above command creates an image, but inorder to create containers, we run this command
docker run IMAGE_NAME

3)This command only runs the single container
docker start conatiner_name

4)This command only stops the single conatiner
docker stop conatiner_name



--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

TroubleShooting commands

1)This command is used to access the logs of an particular conatiner
docker log Conatiner_Name    (or Conatiner_ID)

We can simply click on the conatiner name in docker desktop inorder to access its logs

2) If we want to check any files or environment variables etc then this command is used
docker exec -it conatiner_id/bin/bash     

After running this command, we can write env to check envireonment file or any file






